ait of a revolutionary poet who embodied the spirit of his age Published in time for the 250th anniversary of William Wordsworth’s birth, this is the biography of a great poetic genius, a revolutionary who changed the world. Wordsworth rejoiced in the French Revolution and played a central role in the cultural upheaval that we call the Romantic Revolution. He and his fellow Romantics changed forever the way we think about childhood, the sense of the self, our connection to the natural environment, and the purpose of poetry. But his was also a revolutionary life in the old sense of the word, insofar as his art was of memory, the return of the past, the circling back to childhood and youth. This beautifully written biography is purposefully fragmentary, momentary, and selective, opening up what Wordsworth called "the hiding-places of my power."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aNature (Aesthetics) 0aNature (Aesthetics). 0aPoets, Englishy19th centuryvBiography. 0aRomanticism. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020z978311069231040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300228915423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300228915.jpg  a978-3-11-069231-0  YUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3